<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.5-1.2 cm vs. 0.7-5.7 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.42-3.2 cm) and leaf apex (obtuse to acute in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Majure &amp; Judd" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Miconia pagnolensis" order="Myrtales" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pagnolensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Miconia pagnolensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. acute to acuminate in 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Miconia lima" order="Myrtales" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Miconia lima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
